## CRITICAL: Python interpreter

**USE `.venv/bin/python`, NOT bare `python`.** Bare `python` resolves via
the pyenv shim to Python 3.12.9, which has a different (stale) package
environment than `.venv` (Python 3.13). ML and Align packages appeared
"not installed" because I was checking pyenv, not .venv — they were
always editable-installed in .venv.

Per `rules/python-environment.md` MUST Rule 1 — explicit `.venv/bin/python`
is mandatory. Every bash command in this session should prefix with
`.venv/bin/python -m` for Python-related operations.

